1+ but it gets harder as you go, and more reliant on pure unadulterated luck). However, if you are a pure grouper (like myself) getting to 65 and then working AA is very worth it. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=195825"> Sensei Lucsa Kurobuchi</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Transcendent</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.raarcentral.com">Crusaders of Plilo</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eveel>eveel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 188<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(11/7/02 5:40:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=541.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Levels or AA (mean beyond 60)</span><hr size=1> IMHO, get run3 asap, then get 60, then fill out your basic AA (FA3 or regen3 depending on which you feel you'll use more).<br>
<br>
Remember that at 61, your average XP per mob goes down as the blue range is reduced so soloing is much more difficult. It *may* even be the case that the high blue bonus(i.e. fighting 56th+ mobs at 60) may get reduced due to the shrinking of the blue range, so you'd need to be fighting 58th level mobs to get the same aaxp rate at 61 that you did 60.<br>
<br>
Personally I hit 60 then filled out my basic with FA3 and am now trying to group in PoP to get ND3 and CA3 before even looking at 61. PE3 and FD3 may even be worth doing before 61, with PE3 being better after doing ND3 and CA3.<br>
<br>
There are, supposedly, still some PoP abilities that may or may not be bugged. Keep reading people's responses here and make your own mind up on them when you're closer.<br>
<br>
AA abilities depend a lot on what you do, if you pull for a raiding guild then AC and HPs should be your main goal. If, OTOH, you mainly melee then you should be looking to up your DPS as much as possible. People who do both need to balance the two, depending on how much you value survivability over DPS and vice versa. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showUserPublicProfile?gid=reyndamonk>ReynDaMonk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 180<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(11/9/02 12:05:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=541.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Levels or AA (mean beyond 60)</span><hr size=1> Depends what you want, really.<br>
<br>
If you want to be a great solo artist, I might suggust you get 61 and work up some AA.  You can easily spend 120 points in damage and tanking AA without even touching POP, you can solo a lot of stuff very nicely at 61, and you have access to some of the fun PoP AA.<br>
<br>
As soon as you pass 61, all the soloable stuff goes light blue, and then quickly green.  The entire kael arena is light blue / green at 64 (zeks are blue, some vets are blue), but don't be fooled..it's light blue because you can kick the crap out of it.  I went there with a 60 warrior friend and a 52 bot cleric, and we cleared 2/3 of the arena and pulled all the zeks just for the hell of it.  Easily, I might add.<br>
<br>
Off topic...For all you doubters, bio orb &gt; all when it comes to splitting those bastards (and any other mob group where they instantly return to spawn when you FD).  Click, pull, feign, and gank your single when the rest go home because it's wandering aimlessly right where you FD'd it.<br>
<br>
So if you raid, if you want to be a part of a group all the time, if you just want to feel more badass, head for 65 as fast as you can...the returns from getting those levels are HUGE.  Where I parsed 60-70 DPS at level 60, I now parse well over 100 DPS (same buffs, just epic haste + 36% item, mith fist / SoM).  5 DPS or so come from the (bugged?) level 1 Wu's AA, the rest comes from new damage tables and a better chance to hit the mobs.<br>
<br>
I found it very worth it to level up, I'd rather be a part of a group, interacting with guildies, and be able to kick the crap out of anyone who disagrees, as opposed to soloing easy blue crap for hours on end.  Everyone wasting their time in FG can go watch me get an AA in 82 minutes, along with 5 other people, just pullin mobs to a skillful group in a difficult PoP zone, while the rest of ya gloat over 1% per solo kill =)<br>
<br>
But really, ít's just a matter of play style...if you can't find a group in the upper 60's, you're screwed.  There's absolutely nothing you can solo, and about the only class you can tank / duo with is a shaman.  You can aggro kite mobs with a wizard, druid, necro, whatever..but they're not always snarable (thanks quadkite nerf patch) and you can end up flat on your back and zoning to nexus before you know what hit you if you try to tackle stuff with less than a good group.<br>
<br>
